there the one time with sanderbar and IS, was a well<br>
led raid but parabolic's a great chanter and that's<br>
kind of hard to come by and frankly invaluable.<br>
<br>
regarding fear.. i've been contemplating leading a fear<br>
raid for a couple months (ever since i've been stalled<br>
there on the last piece of my epic).  here's IS's<br>
fear guide:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub16.ezboard.com/fistormerfrm12.showMessage?topicID=2.topic">pub16.ezboard.com/fistorm...ID=2.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
a couple things i've learned.. there's the myth of zone-<br>
wide aggro bug on breaking.  it's a myth.  however, the level<br>
range of the break groups is incredibly important.  a fear<br>
break is tough for 3 groups of 55's.. one group of 65's,<br>
however, can easily clear it without evacs or chain<br>
aggro.  so, to lead a successful fear raid i think i'd want<br>
to have at the very least a 60+ tank, chanter and cleric,<br>
as well as at least 3 evac'ers for the first 3 groups.<br>
<br>
we have none of these things.<br>
<br>
until we do, i don't want to put our reputation on the line<br>
leading an open fear raid.  let's go there ourselves, or<br>
perhaps with allies, and poke around a bit, get to know<br>
the zone.. that'd be fun, but no open raid until we're<br>
pretty sure we know what we're doing.<br>
<br>
<br>
i don't know if anyone knows either of these zones better<br>
than i.. those are just my thoughts :-)<br>
<br>
